            <div type="general">
               <p xml:space="preserve">Sbiba is an old town in the northeast of the Tunisian governorate of Kasserine. Ruins in its Fath-district (Ḥayy l-Fatḥ) bear witness to the Roman founders of the town. Moreover, street art calls to remind people of the town’s history, but also shows contemporary motifs.</p>
               <p rendition="#slideshow">
                  <figure>
                     <link target="The-Smile-of-Sbiba.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/The-Smile-of-Sbiba.jpg"/>
                     <head type="imgCaption">The smile of Sbiba</head>
                  </figure>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="Sbiba-arts-2.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/Sbiba-arts-2.jpg"/>
