                  </figure>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="Sbiba-arts.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/Sbiba-arts.jpg"/>
                     <head type="imgCaption">Modern arts</head>
                  </figure>
               </p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">Situated on the river valley Oued el Hateb (Wǟd il-Ḥaṭib), the fertile soil and peasant population characterize the region. Sbiba is famous for its apple plantations, but its inhabitants are by far not only specialised in the cultivation of apples. Interestingly, in Sbiba the farming activities are linked to the tribal background of the people. The tribal group of the Sbitat (is-Sbīṭāt), for instance, are specialized in the cultivation of apples, peaches, and apricots, as well as paprika and tomatoes. In contrast, the Smeta (is-Smǟta), another tribal group of Sbiba, cultivate only cereals like barley and wheat, while the tribal group of the Ouled Kholfa (Ūlǟd Xulfa) breed sheep.</p>
